1
00:00:35,076 --> 00:00:40,081
{\an8}The person that we are suspecting
to be dangerous and a deadly assasin,

2
00:00:40,165 --> 00:00:41,416
{\an8}which is La Fornarina, look!

3
00:00:41,499 --> 00:00:43,084
{\an8}She is with Mikoy!

4
00:00:54,763 --> 00:00:58,349
{\an8}It's an honor meeting
the infamous La Fornarina.

5
00:01:09,319 --> 00:01:11,571
{\an8}That's exactly what's so frustrating, Bok.

6
00:01:11,654 --> 00:01:14,157
{\an8}Shouldn't we just stay focused
on our mission?

7
00:01:14,741 --> 00:01:17,494
{\an8}But everyone has an opinion,
everyone has to be heard.

8
00:01:17,577 --> 00:01:18,787
{\an8}Valid.

9
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:22,832
{\an8}Everything you said,
all your sentiments, are valid.

10
00:01:22,916 --> 00:01:24,167
{\an8}But, Bok,

11
00:01:24,751 --> 00:01:26,211
{\an8}just a piece of advice.

12
00:01:26,795 --> 00:01:28,004
{\an8}Don't think about everything at once.

13
00:01:30,381 --> 00:01:32,467
{\an8}Focus on the task at hand first, okay?

14
00:01:32,550 --> 00:01:33,968
{\an8}Otherwise, nothing gets done.

15
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:36,012
{\an8}You'll get overwhelmed.
You won't be able to breathe.

16
00:01:36,095 --> 00:01:38,848
{\an8}You really won't be able to move, okay?

17
00:01:38,932 --> 00:01:41,351
{\an8}So let's just deal with what's manageable.

18
00:01:41,434 --> 00:01:42,685
{\an8}Like Mikoy.

19
00:01:42,769 --> 00:01:45,522
{\an8}The task at hand is we need to talk to him

20
00:01:45,605 --> 00:01:47,649
{\an8}as soon as possible. That's the priority.

21
00:01:53,404 --> 00:01:54,489
{\an8}I have an idea.

22
00:02:10,296 --> 00:02:15,301
{\an8}The minute that I find out
that you're gossiping to my father

23
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:17,679
{\an8}or you tell anyone about my business,

24
00:02:18,388 --> 00:02:19,514
{\an8}mark my words,

25
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:41,744
{\an8}You won't hear anything from me anymore.

26
00:02:50,128 --> 00:02:51,588
{\an8}I'm actually easy to deal with.

27
00:02:55,758 --> 00:03:01,097
I want you here because I need a clone.

28
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:19,282
All calls and messages

29
00:03:19,365 --> 00:03:22,160
from the original SIM
will transfer to the cloned device.

30
00:03:23,995 --> 00:03:26,039
I can monitor everything remotely.

31
00:03:27,582 --> 00:03:31,127
Whoever sends a text or call,

32
00:03:32,211 --> 00:03:34,714
we'll know exactly who they are.

33
00:03:34,797 --> 00:03:37,759
That phone will not be private anymore.

34
00:03:55,485 --> 00:03:56,319
Sofie!

35
00:03:57,737 --> 00:03:58,613
Hi, Luisa!

36
00:03:58,696 --> 00:03:59,572
Hi!

37
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:06,955
I know you said before
he was kind of a loser.

38
00:04:07,538 --> 00:04:10,416
But actually, he's kind of sweet.

39
00:04:12,043 --> 00:04:13,461
I'm talking about Angelito.

40
00:04:13,544 --> 00:04:15,964
Like, surprisingly.

41
00:04:16,756 --> 00:04:18,216
- I know. Surprisingly.
- Yes.

42
00:04:18,299 --> 00:04:20,593
Actually, you know what?
He invited me to go somewhere.

43
00:04:20,677 --> 00:04:23,471
Like a concert or something.

44
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:26,015
Do you wanna come?

45
00:04:27,684 --> 00:04:29,060
- Me?
- Yes.

46
00:04:29,811 --> 00:04:31,771
Oh, wait, sorry.

47
00:04:31,854 --> 00:04:33,648
I don't mean to put you on the spot

48
00:04:33,731 --> 00:04:35,608
or make you feel like a third wheel.
Nothing like that.

49
00:04:35,692 --> 00:04:36,901
No, no, no.

50
00:04:36,985 --> 00:04:37,819
It's fine.

51
00:04:37,902 --> 00:04:39,737
- Really?
- I'll bring my boyfriend.

52
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:56,170
Mikoy?

53
00:04:59,674 --> 00:05:01,009
He's not answering.

54
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:03,928
What's taking him so long?

55
00:05:08,975 --> 00:05:10,310
Chiara!

56
00:05:10,393 --> 00:05:12,103
- Hello!
- Hi!

57
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:15,356
Hi!

58
00:05:16,983 --> 00:05:18,860
You're alone? Where's Sianong?

59
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:22,447
I came so long. He's on his way.

60
00:05:26,242 --> 00:05:29,037
We noticed Mikoy's been busy lately.

61
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:31,372
He hasn't been responding to our invites.

62
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:34,709
So we figured the drinks
should come to him instead.

63
00:05:34,792 --> 00:05:36,961
Wow, that's so nice of you.

64
00:05:37,045 --> 00:05:39,464
I don't know what got into him.
He suddenly missed work,

65
00:05:39,547 --> 00:05:41,883
now he's buried in it.

66
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:46,512
Do you want to…

67
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,141
start without him for now?

68
00:05:52,101 --> 00:05:54,312
Sure! Game!

69
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:57,440
- Come in.
- Okay!

70
00:06:02,195 --> 00:06:04,363
He should be here soon too, right?

71
00:06:04,447 --> 00:06:05,448
Yes.

72
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,503
Holy crap!

73
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:20,088
My God!

74
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:21,255
Hey, hey, hey!

75
00:06:21,339 --> 00:06:23,424
Where are you going, brother?
What's going on?

76
00:06:23,508 --> 00:06:26,052
I'm meeting Alex.
We're going to talk to Mikoy.

77
00:06:26,135 --> 00:06:27,220
There it is.

78
00:06:27,303 --> 00:06:29,305
Why do you look like that?
Is something wrong?

79
00:06:30,306 --> 00:06:32,141
Not yet, but there's a complication.

80
00:06:32,725 --> 00:06:34,519
- What is it?
- Wanna know?

81
00:06:34,602 --> 00:06:35,520
What?

82
00:06:35,603 --> 00:06:36,813
You!

83
00:06:36,896 --> 00:06:39,357
You're one huge complication!
You're such a hassle. Move!

84
00:06:44,570 --> 00:06:46,322
Will report to Chief

85
00:06:46,405 --> 00:06:49,492
that the agents have no manners.

86
00:06:53,830 --> 00:06:55,748
So how are things between you and Mikoy?

87
00:06:57,125 --> 00:06:59,168
We're good. Great even!

88
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:01,462
Oh, that's good then!

89
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:04,799
How about you and Mikoy?

90
00:07:04,882 --> 00:07:08,678
Oh, we're good. Same as always, buddies!

91
00:07:10,388 --> 00:07:11,264
Alex.

92
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:21,816
Why do you ask?

93
00:07:22,900 --> 00:07:24,569
Nothing. Like…

94
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:33,035
Oh, definitely.
That guy's practically an open book!

95
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:34,829
Sometimes it's even TMI.

96
00:07:35,329 --> 00:07:36,706
Really?

97
00:07:36,789 --> 00:07:38,624
So he's that open to you!

98
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:41,252
Oh, absolutely, everything.

99
00:07:41,335 --> 00:07:43,171
Everything? Even his sex life?

100
00:07:47,717 --> 00:07:48,759
Sex life?

101
00:07:51,804 --> 00:07:54,974
I think he talks to Sianong
about stuff like that.

102
00:07:55,057 --> 00:07:56,851
That's more guy talk.

103
00:07:56,934 --> 00:07:58,311
But look,

104
00:07:58,394 --> 00:08:01,105
I don't think Mikoy kisses and tells.

105
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:03,107
He's super protective.

106
00:08:03,191 --> 00:08:04,192
Protective of you.

107
00:08:08,279 --> 00:08:09,238
Wait.

108
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:11,657
Is there a problem?

109
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:21,334
Senator, it's getting harder
to run this agency.

110
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:24,295
Because the expenses keep growing.

111
00:08:26,422 --> 00:08:28,216
Well, sometimes…

112
00:08:29,133 --> 00:08:31,552
Change doesn't make you rich.

113
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:33,554
Because most of the time,

114
00:08:33,638 --> 00:08:35,890
change is just loose coins.

115
00:08:41,729 --> 00:08:45,066
Maybe the Greek philosopher Parmenides

116
00:08:45,149 --> 00:08:48,027
didn't believe in change because

117
00:08:48,110 --> 00:08:49,487
he had no spare change!

118
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:58,538
But Heraclitus had plenty of coins.

119
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:00,248
Because he believes

120
00:09:00,331 --> 00:09:01,874
that change is constant.

121
00:09:12,134 --> 00:09:13,469
Excuse me, Sen.

122
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:15,096
Excuse me, General Ruiz.

123
00:09:15,179 --> 00:09:16,556
I'll step out for a bit.

124
00:09:17,181 --> 00:09:20,101
I don't think I digested the "corn" I ate.

125
00:09:20,685 --> 00:09:22,603
Because of all the corn"-y jokes.

126
00:09:26,607 --> 00:09:29,485
Good thing that idiot caught on
and left too.

127
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:33,322
I was almost running out
of punchlines myself.

128
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:36,325
But actually, bro,

129
00:09:36,409 --> 00:09:37,910
I really wanted to talk to you.

130
00:09:38,494 --> 00:09:39,870
Just the two of us.

131
00:09:39,954 --> 00:09:43,291
Because we've known each other
for a long time,

132
00:09:43,374 --> 00:09:45,585
and our friendship runs deep.

133
00:09:45,668 --> 00:09:48,462
You sound so serious.

134
00:10:01,058 --> 00:10:02,685
I don't have a problem with him.

135
00:10:03,477 --> 00:10:04,645
It's with his father.

136
00:10:06,731 --> 00:10:08,441
Mario Pinagpala.

137
00:10:11,861 --> 00:10:13,029
Honestly, my friend,

138
00:10:13,112 --> 00:10:15,531
I felt so betrayed

139
00:10:15,615 --> 00:10:18,451
that you kept this information from me.

140
00:10:19,243 --> 00:10:23,623
I didn't want to add more charges
against the Moravianos.

141
00:10:24,540 --> 00:10:26,917
But you're playing with fire, my friend.

142
00:10:27,001 --> 00:10:32,214
You and I both know
what Mario is capable of.

143
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:35,676
<i>Or should we call him by his real name?</i>

144
00:10:36,761 --> 00:10:38,346
<i>Isidro Catacutan.</i>

145
00:10:39,138 --> 00:10:41,265
{\an8}ISIDRO A. CATACUTAN
YOU WILL ALWAYS BE REMEMBERED

146
00:11:34,443 --> 00:11:36,195
Did you and Mikoy have a problem?

147
00:11:37,822 --> 00:11:40,533
Not that I'm fishing, but…

148
00:11:41,158 --> 00:11:42,451
Woman to woman.

149
00:11:43,035 --> 00:11:44,995
You can confide in me, Chiara.

150
00:11:45,079 --> 00:11:46,038
Anything!

151
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:48,666
Thank you!

152
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:50,960
But no!

153
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:53,212
Nothing. We're okay.

154
00:11:57,299 --> 00:11:58,342
Actually…

155
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:04,098
there is one thing

156
00:12:05,182 --> 00:12:08,352
that I would say kind of bothers me.

157
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:10,688
But it's not a big deal.

158
00:12:11,272 --> 00:12:13,607
You know Mikoy, right?

159
00:12:13,691 --> 00:12:15,025
He's so kind, right?

160
00:12:15,109 --> 00:12:16,110
Yes.

161
00:12:16,193 --> 00:12:17,361
So…

162
00:12:20,823 --> 00:12:23,159
He's too nice?

163
00:12:24,201 --> 00:12:25,536
You get me?

164
00:12:25,619 --> 00:12:27,955
Like he's too much of a gentleman.

165
00:12:30,583 --> 00:12:31,667
What I'm trying to say is,

166
00:12:31,750 --> 00:12:34,211
of course, we all want that at first,

167
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:35,880
- you know.
- Of course.

168
00:12:35,963 --> 00:12:37,298
But that's the thing.

169
00:12:37,381 --> 00:12:40,718
We're together now, and I'm here.

170
00:12:42,178 --> 00:12:44,138
I've been waiting for so long.

171
00:12:47,224 --> 00:12:49,059
Waiting? Hold on.

172
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:51,437
- What do you mean?
- The waiting part.

173
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:54,356
I get it though, because…

174
00:12:56,775 --> 00:12:59,695
- He grew up in a conservative country.
- Yes.

175
00:12:59,778 --> 00:13:01,947
And I'm liberated because, of course,

176
00:13:02,031 --> 00:13:04,033
I'm European. I'm from Europe.

177
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:05,409
- Yes?
- But…

178
00:13:05,951 --> 00:13:09,622
But still, it's 2026.

179
00:13:09,705 --> 00:13:11,749
We're both of legal age.

180
00:13:12,833 --> 00:13:15,753
I think it's about time

181
00:13:15,836 --> 00:13:20,007
that our relationship
leveled up a little more.

182
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:21,342
More exciting!

183
00:13:21,425 --> 00:13:23,761
More passion!

184
00:13:26,722 --> 00:13:27,848
What do you mean?

185
00:13:27,932 --> 00:13:29,225
You know what?

186
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:32,311
Let me just ask you something else, Alex.

187
00:13:33,354 --> 00:13:36,273
Have you ever met
any of his ex-girlfriends?

188
00:13:38,567 --> 00:13:40,528
I just wanna know because…

189
00:13:40,611 --> 00:13:43,405
If they've ever mentioned
that he's really like that.

190
00:13:43,489 --> 00:13:45,574
Like he's really that much of a gentleman.

191
00:13:45,658 --> 00:13:48,035
So unbelievably nice.

192
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:52,998
What if he's actually waiting
until marriage, right?

193
00:13:55,793 --> 00:13:58,045
Oh, girl, you know what?

194
00:13:58,128 --> 00:14:01,131
None of his exes ever mentioned
anything like that.

195
00:14:01,215 --> 00:14:04,301
- Okay.
- But sure, for you, I'll try to find out.

196
00:14:04,385 --> 00:14:05,386
Really?

197
00:14:05,469 --> 00:14:06,387
Yes!

198
00:14:06,470 --> 00:14:07,805
- My gosh!
- I'll handle it.

199
00:14:07,888 --> 00:14:09,098
Thank you, Alex!

200
00:14:09,181 --> 00:14:11,433
Thank you. Oh my gosh! Whoa.

201
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:12,601
Oh, you know what?

202
00:14:12,685 --> 00:14:14,186
If I wasn't straight,

203
00:14:14,270 --> 00:14:15,271
I would've fallen for you already.

204
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:17,398
- I'm not kidding.
- Really?

205
00:14:17,481 --> 00:14:18,607
Cheers!

206
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:19,942
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

207
00:14:20,651 --> 00:14:22,987
- Finally, I'm so happy.
- Yes.

208
00:14:23,070 --> 00:14:24,238
Sweetheart!

209
00:14:24,864 --> 00:14:26,448
Good thing you're home already.

210
00:14:26,532 --> 00:14:27,491
Because…

211
00:14:28,075 --> 00:14:30,411
we have a surprise visitor.

212
00:14:40,504 --> 00:14:42,423
Does he know his son is an asset?

213
00:14:42,506 --> 00:14:43,924
‪Does Mario know?

214
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:45,009
No.

215
00:14:45,551 --> 00:14:46,802
He doesn't know anything.

216
00:14:48,178 --> 00:14:53,559
When he finds out, he'll get angry
because you used his son.

217
00:14:53,642 --> 00:14:57,646
And second, you're putting
his family's lives at risk.

218
00:15:01,108 --> 00:15:03,777
You won't be able to hide that from him.

219
00:15:03,861 --> 00:15:07,615
Eventually, he'll find out
what happened to his son.

220
00:15:08,908 --> 00:15:11,243
The past between you and Mario

221
00:15:11,327 --> 00:15:12,995
runs deep and complicated.

222
00:15:13,078 --> 00:15:15,748
And I know you want
to bury it in the past,

223
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:19,627
but you need to tell him the truth
about his son.

224
00:15:19,710 --> 00:15:21,295
Because if not,

225
00:15:21,378 --> 00:15:24,173
it might blow up in both our faces.

226
00:15:30,804 --> 00:15:32,139
Because of his skill set,

227
00:15:32,222 --> 00:15:36,185
I'm sure he can help you
with your Moraviano problem.

228
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:50,199
<i>Mikoy's father has a specific skill set</i>
<i>that is actually very dangerous.</i>

229
00:15:50,783 --> 00:15:52,159
<i>It's deadly.</i>

230
00:15:52,785 --> 00:15:54,495
<i>If we bring him in,</i>

231
00:15:54,578 --> 00:15:57,081
<i>he is a variable that we cannot control.</i>

232
00:15:57,164 --> 00:16:01,043
<i>We can't even be sure</i>
<i>if he'll side with us.</i>

233
00:16:08,050 --> 00:16:09,426
I can see that!

234
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:14,473
Sweetheart, I missed you.

235
00:16:15,766 --> 00:16:17,101
Well, Alex is here,

236
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:21,063
and she brought food
and drinks to surprise you.

237
00:16:23,649 --> 00:16:25,401
Surprise indeed!

238
00:16:27,403 --> 00:16:28,904
What are you doing here?

239
00:16:29,530 --> 00:16:32,908
Did we have plans
that I didn't know about?

240
00:16:32,992 --> 00:16:34,451
Oh, no, nothing!

241
00:16:34,535 --> 00:16:36,787
Sianong and I just thought
we'd surprise you.

242
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:39,289
Because it's been a while
since our last night out, right?

243
00:16:39,873 --> 00:16:42,042
Turns out I'm the one surprised

244
00:16:42,126 --> 00:16:45,504
because Chiara's here and not you.

245
00:16:45,587 --> 00:16:48,924
You didn't even mention
that she moved in with you.

246
00:16:56,849 --> 00:16:59,226
And you know, the timing
of our surprise is perfect too

247
00:16:59,309 --> 00:17:03,981
because we can celebrate
this milestone in your relationship!

248
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:08,902
- Yes!
- Right?

249
00:17:10,529 --> 00:17:11,405
Wait a second.

250
00:17:11,488 --> 00:17:14,575
Didn't you say you and Sianong
were surprising me?

251
00:17:14,658 --> 00:17:15,534
Where is he?

252
00:17:16,243 --> 00:17:17,619
He's on the way. You know him.

253
00:17:17,703 --> 00:17:19,496
That guy's always running late.

254
00:17:20,414 --> 00:17:22,916
You know what? Alex is right.

255
00:17:23,459 --> 00:17:25,836
This really is a milestone
in our relationship.

256
00:17:25,919 --> 00:17:28,422
You know, it's a good thing
you and Sianong are here

257
00:17:28,505 --> 00:17:31,050
because I wouldn't have realized it. Yes!

258
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:34,011
That's a big milestone for us, sweetheart.

259
00:17:34,094 --> 00:17:35,429
Oh my gosh!

260
00:17:35,512 --> 00:17:38,098
I'm just happy for both of you!

261
00:17:38,182 --> 00:17:39,808
Oh, wow!

262
00:17:40,642 --> 00:17:41,727
Yes.

263
00:17:42,686 --> 00:17:44,396
Well, eat now, sweetheart.

264
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:45,814
Okay.

265
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:48,692
Let me take this off first,
so you'll be more comfortable.

266
00:17:48,776 --> 00:17:49,902
Yes.

267
00:17:49,985 --> 00:17:51,278
Have you eaten yet?

268
00:17:51,862 --> 00:17:54,531
You guys go ahead first.
I'll just put this in your room.

269
00:17:54,615 --> 00:17:56,075
- Okay.
- Bye.

270
00:17:57,868 --> 00:17:59,787
- Hurry up, sweetheart.
- This is so fun!

271
00:18:40,619 --> 00:18:42,788
<i>I can monitor everything remotely.</i>

272
00:18:43,413 --> 00:18:46,416
<i>Whoever sends a text or makes a call,</i>

273
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,794
<i>we'll know exactly who they are.</i>

274
00:18:49,628 --> 00:18:53,090
{\an8}<i>That phone will not be private anymore.</i>

275
00:18:57,469 --> 00:19:00,889
TRANSFERRING DATA

276
00:19:09,398 --> 00:19:11,066
<i>What are you doing, Chiara?</i>

277
00:19:11,900 --> 00:19:14,319
<i>Why are you doing this</i>
<i>to the person you love?</i>

278
00:19:21,118 --> 00:19:23,162
TRANSFER COMPLETE

279
00:19:41,096 --> 00:19:42,514
Is it done now?

280
00:19:42,598 --> 00:19:44,808
I look stupid, you know.

281
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:46,810
My jaw already hurts.

282
00:19:46,894 --> 00:19:48,061
Okay, safe.

283
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:51,023
But let's keep our voices down low.

284
00:19:52,566 --> 00:19:53,650
Okay.

285
00:19:54,359 --> 00:19:55,903
Not like that!

286
00:19:55,986 --> 00:19:57,196
Then how?

287
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:59,489
- Low.
- Oh, okay.

288
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:01,408
Is this okay now?

289
00:20:01,491 --> 00:20:02,993
Yes, you're doing well.

290
00:20:03,076 --> 00:20:04,161
Okay.

291
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:08,332
What are you doing here?

292
00:20:08,415 --> 00:20:09,708
Is there an emergency?

293
00:20:13,253 --> 00:20:16,381
That personal assistant
of yours is La Fornarina.

294
00:20:16,465 --> 00:20:17,424
What?

295
00:20:26,725 --> 00:20:28,018
Keep it down!

296
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:29,603
Chiara might hear you.

297
00:20:30,562 --> 00:20:34,608
But what do you mean?
Carlota is La Fornarina?

298
00:20:35,192 --> 00:20:36,485
Yes, it's really her.

299
00:20:36,568 --> 00:20:39,780
She's been spotted the night
Vicek disappeared.

300
00:20:41,031 --> 00:20:44,409
And we have reason to believe
that she's the one who killed him.

301
00:20:46,328 --> 00:20:48,914
But why is she pretending
to be my secretary

302
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:50,415
if she's an assassin?

303
00:20:50,999 --> 00:20:52,251
Do you think…

304
00:20:52,334 --> 00:20:55,295
She is not here to be your assistant.

305
00:20:55,879 --> 00:20:58,757
They sent Carlota to monitor you.

306
00:20:59,299 --> 00:21:01,510
So starting now, that phone we gave you,

307
00:21:01,593 --> 00:21:03,136
don't use it anymore.

308
00:21:04,179 --> 00:21:05,973
How am I supposed to contact you?

309
00:21:06,556 --> 00:21:07,808
We'll handle it. We will contact you.

310
00:21:07,891 --> 00:21:08,892
We'll figure something out.

311
00:21:09,559 --> 00:21:11,019
What?

312
00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:12,312
I can't understand you anymore.

313
00:21:12,396 --> 00:21:13,981
We'll figure something out.

314
00:21:14,064 --> 00:21:16,692
Wait, that tickles. Do it again.

315
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:19,569
Come on now.

316
00:21:56,023 --> 00:21:58,066
- Sweetheart!
- Oh my God!

317
00:21:58,150 --> 00:21:59,526
We're, um…

318
00:21:59,609 --> 00:22:01,862
We're thinking of playing a game!

319
00:22:01,945 --> 00:22:02,863
Right?

320
00:22:02,946 --> 00:22:04,823
- A game?
- Right?

321
00:22:05,615 --> 00:22:08,327
Well, I'm in. What game is it?

322
00:22:12,164 --> 00:22:13,999
Money or Whisper!

323
00:22:18,378 --> 00:22:20,464
Oh, that must be Sianong!

324
00:22:21,214 --> 00:22:22,674
There he is.

325
00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:27,429
‪Yo, yo, yo!

326
00:22:38,523 --> 00:22:40,317
No, just in time.

327
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,152
They're playing a game.

328
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:44,780
Money or Whisper?

329
00:22:55,123 --> 00:22:57,459
He's too interested in logistics concerns

330
00:22:57,542 --> 00:22:59,294
and the company's manpower.

331
00:23:03,173 --> 00:23:06,510
But he wants all managers
to report directly to him.

332
00:23:06,593 --> 00:23:09,846
Including very specific reports
about our drivers

333
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:12,182
and low-level manpower.

334
00:23:12,265 --> 00:23:14,351
Like he's sensing something is off.

335
00:23:34,496 --> 00:23:36,039
It's not just that, sir.

336
00:23:36,123 --> 00:23:37,624
Look at this.

337
00:23:39,084 --> 00:23:41,419
This car arrived at the same time

338
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:44,297
when I got to the café with Mikoy.

339
00:23:45,590 --> 00:23:46,883
And when we left,

340
00:23:46,967 --> 00:23:49,136
that same car also left.

341
00:24:05,152 --> 00:24:07,946
Whoever was in that car,

342
00:24:08,947 --> 00:24:10,699
they're Mikoy's handlers.

343
00:24:38,810 --> 00:24:40,228
An asset.

344
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:44,292
They can't use a government vehicle.

345
00:25:44,376 --> 00:25:47,754
<i>They use a safer way, like what</i>
<i>the civilians and criminals always do.</i>

346
00:25:53,051 --> 00:25:55,136
Chiara must focus on her last mission.

347
00:25:55,220 --> 00:25:59,099
If only you could see your daughter,
you will realize how much in love she is!

348
00:25:59,182 --> 00:26:01,101
It's time for Mikoy to know the truth.

349
00:26:01,184 --> 00:26:04,854
<i>And you will realize</i>
<i>how dangerous this world is.</i>

350
00:26:04,938 --> 00:26:06,064
<i>Spin the bottle?</i>

351
00:26:06,147 --> 00:26:07,774
That's truth or dare!

352
00:26:07,857 --> 00:26:09,192
- Okay.
- Ready?

353
00:26:09,276 --> 00:26:10,318
- Game.
- Ready.

354
00:26:10,402 --> 00:26:11,736
I'll choose truth.

355
00:26:11,820 --> 00:26:13,613
Do you like someone now?

